Maintainer: Hugo Gobato Souto <hugo.souto@dell.com>
Description: Implements 'CountBCF' and 'Zero-Inflated CountBCF', Bayesian Causal
    Forest sampler for count and zero-inflated count outcomes
    (Souto, 2026a; Souto, 2026b). The package extends the Bayesian Causal Forest
    of Hahn, Murray and Carvalho (2020) to count and zero-inflated count
    responses by applying the (mu, tau) decomposition on top of the log-linear
    BART backbone of Murray (2021). The implementation builds directly on the
    'countbart' source code by Nathan B. Wikle and Corwin M. Zigler
    (https://github.com/nbwikle/estimating-interference), reusing its MCMC
    machinery, GIG leaf prior, and zero-inflation handling, and recasting them
    inside the BCF (mu_f, tau_f) parameterization for the count component
    (Poisson and Negative Binomial) and the structural-zero log-odds components
    (ZIP and ZINB). The package returns posterior draws of conditional average
    treatment effects on both the log-rate and response scales.
